Eight 80-bit x87 registers in a stack with st(0) at the top:
st(0) - st(7)
and the additional associated control/status registers:
fctrl : floating point control word (16 bits)
fstat : floating point status word (16 bits)
ftag  : floating point tags (16 bits)
fiseg : floating point instruction pointer segment selector (16 bits)
fioff : floating point instruction pointer offset (32 bits)
foseg : floating point data pointer (operand) segment selector (16 bits)
fooff : floating point data pointer (operand) offset (32 bits)
fop   : floating point opcode (11 bits)

Note:  MMX instructions use the low-order 64 bits of each "st" register as an
"mm" register, mm0 - mm7, for SIMD integer instructions.

Eight 128-bit SSE registers:
xmm0 - xmm7
and a 32-bit SSE control/status register:
mxcsr
